# Playwright tests (`*.playwright.test.ts` / `*.playwright.spec.ts`)

JSDoc above tests and line comments in these files: follow AGENTS.md code-comment rules (plain text, no Markdown bold/italic; single quotes instead of grave accents for inline references).

## Preconditions

- Run against a **production Electron build** after relevant source changes (`yarn quasar:build:electron` / `quasar build -m electron`). See [README.md](README.md).
- [playwright.config.ts](playwright.config.ts): `workers: 1`, `fullyParallel: false`, unified `outputDir` `test-results/playwright-artifacts`, and `testMatch` covering `src/components/**` and `e2e-tests/**` Playwright files. Terminal reporter: `line` (concise progress; no per-pass list spam; failures in full), plus HTML report `test-results/playwright-report` (sibling folder to avoid reporter vs artifact path overlap).
- Storybook VRT: [`.storybook-workspace/playwright.storybook-visual.config.ts`](../../.storybook-workspace/playwright.storybook-visual.config.ts) uses the same **`line`** reporter pattern and HTML under **`test-results/storybook-visual-*`**. Screenshot mismatches attach **Expected / Actual / Diff** on the failing per-story **`test.step`** (soft assertions). Per-story **`[storybook-visual]`** console progress is off unless **`FA_STORYBOOK_VISUAL_VERBOSE=1`** (see [storybook-stories.mdc](storybook-stories.mdc) and [`.storybook-workspace/visual-tests/storybook.visual.playwright.test.ts`](../../.storybook-workspace/visual-tests/storybook.visual.playwright.test.ts)).

## Vitest for `helpers/` harness packages

- Node-only harness code under **`helpers/`** (e.g. **`helpers/playwrightHelpers/`**, and future sibling packages) is covered by **`*.vitest.test.ts`** in each package’s **`_tests/`** tree; **`yarn test:unit`** runs them as Vitest **`unit-helpers`** via [vitest.helpers.config.mts](vitest/vitest.helpers.config.mts) (file lives in repo-root **`vitest/`**, not inside **`helpers/`**). Add or extend those Vitest files when you change helper logic (env switches, temp dirs, IPC-adjacent helpers). Follow [vitest-tests.mdc](vitest-tests.mdc) for structure, comments, and **100%** **`helpers`** coverage expectations.

## Isolated `userData` reset (per serial suite)

- Import **`resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData`** from **`app/helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightUserDataReset`**. Call it in **`test.beforeAll`** for each **`test.describe.serial`** group **before** **`electron.launch`**, not in **`test.beforeEach`**, when that group shares one **`ElectronApplication`** for the whole describe: **`beforeEach`** would wipe **`playwright-user-data`** on disk while Electron still holds the old profile and the process would diverge from disk.
- When a file needs **multiple** serial groups (different **`COMPONENT_PROPS`** or separate sessions), each group’s **`beforeAll`** runs **`resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData()`** then launches; **`afterAll`** closes with **`closeFaElectronAppWithRecordedVideoAttachments`**.
- Path resolution matches **`appIdentity/fixAppName`** / Electron **`app.getPath('appData')`**; the folder segment is **`PLAYWRIGHT_ISOLATED_USER_DATA_DIR_NAME`** in [playwrightIsolatedUserDataDirName.ts](src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/playwrightIsolatedUserDataDirName.ts). **Do not** import **`fixAppName`** from Node-side Playwright helpers—it imports **`electron`** and breaks test discovery; see [helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightUserDataReset.ts](helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightUserDataReset.ts). Shared Playwright harness modules live under **`helpers/playwrightHelpers/`**; add new cross-cutting helper packages as siblings under **`helpers/`**—keep the repo root for config, **`README`**, lockfiles, and **`scripts/`**.

## HTML report and screen recordings

- Each Electron test attaches **WebM** screen video (see [helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts](helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts)) unless `FA_PLAYWRIGHT_NO_VIDEO` is set. Open **`test-results/playwright-report/index.html`** after a run, open a test, and use **Attachments** to play or download; playable files are under **`test-results/playwright-report/data/`**.
- **Every** Playwright run **replaces** the HTML report folder. Running component tests, then E2E (or the reverse, or a repeat of either) **overwrites** the prior report—there is no merge across runs.
- Root **`yarn test:components`** / **`yarn test:e2e`** (and **`:single`** / **`:single:ci`**) use **`scripts/playwrightWithArtifactTrim.mjs`**, which deletes **`test-results/playwright-artifacts`** after the run. Raw `recordVideo` output uses a temp dir under the OS temp folder, then is attached and trimmed (see **`helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts`**).
- For agents: point humans to **`test-results/playwright-report/index.html`** for per-test videos; do not assume reliable analysis of raw **`.webm`** bytes without specialized tooling.

## Vue templates (hooks for locators)

Primary locators use **`data-test-locator`**; additional hooks (for example `data-test-menu-test` / `data-test-menu-any`, `data-test-tooltip-text`) are defined in **`.vue` files** — follow [vue-template-test-hooks.mdc](vue-template-test-hooks.mdc) when adding or renaming them. This rule covers the **TypeScript test files** only.

## File locations

| Kind | Path pattern |
|------|----------------|
| Component | `src/components/<Component>/_tests/*.playwright.test.ts` |
| E2E | `e2e-tests/*.playwright.spec.ts` |

## Import order (top of file)

1. `import { _electron as electron } from 'playwright'`
2. `import type { ElectronApplication, Page } from 'playwright'` when the spec uses suite-scoped **`let electronApp`** / **`let appWindow`**
3. `import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test'`
4. `import type { TestInfo } from '@playwright/test'` when **`test.beforeAll(async ({}, testInfo) => { ... })`** stores suite **`TestInfo`** for video teardown
5. `import { FA_ELECTRON_MAIN_JS_PATH, FA_FRONTEND_RENDER_TIMER } from 'app/helpers/playwrightHelpers/faPlaywrightElectronLaunchConstants'` (E2E may import only `FA_ELECTRON_MAIN_JS_PATH` when no render timer constant is needed)
6. `closeFaElectronAppWithRecordedVideoAttachments` and `getFaPlaywrightElectronRecordVideoPartial` from `'app/helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo'` (after launch-constants import when both are used)
7. `import { resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData } from 'app/helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightUserDataReset'` (use inside **`beforeAll`** per serial group; see **Isolated `userData` reset** above); keep next to other **`app/`** imports (ESLint may reorder `import type` lines after value imports).
8. Optional: types from `app/types/...`, production **`_data/`** when the spec must stay aligned with runtime (prefer a small parallel module over importing heavy feeds), shared helpers from `src/scripts/_utilities/...` (e.g. [AppControlSingleMenu.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/AppControlSingleMenu/_tests/AppControlSingleMenu.playwright.test.ts))

## File header — documented constants

Repeat this structure in **every** Playwright file (see [GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/GlobalWindowButtons/_tests/GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts), [checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts)):

1. **`extraEnvSettings`** — JSDoc: `Extra env settings to trigger component testing via Playwright` **or** `...E2E...` for e2e.
   - **Component**: `TEST_ENV: 'components'`, `COMPONENT_NAME: '<Name>'` (must match the component the harness loads), `COMPONENT_PROPS: JSON.stringify({})` or a payload built from **inline objects in this file** (e.g. `{ dataInput: menuFixture }`); **do not** import separate `_tests/*.ts` files that exist only to hold fixture blobs. `TEST_ENV` triggers **`%APPDATA%/<package name>/playwright-user-data`** ([fixAppName.ts](src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/fixAppName.ts), folder name in [playwrightIsolatedUserDataDirName.ts](src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/playwrightIsolatedUserDataDirName.ts)) — not **`fantasia-archive-dev`** — so **`electron-store`** does not overlap **`quasar dev`** or packaged profiles.
   - **E2E**: `TEST_ENV: 'e2e'` only ([checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts)); same isolated **`userData`** root as component tests.

2. **`electronMainFilePath`** — JSDoc `Electron main filepath`; type `string`; value `FA_ELECTRON_MAIN_JS_PATH` from **`faPlaywrightElectronLaunchConstants`** (Node-side path aligned with unpackaged `electron-main.js`; do not import `contentBridgeAPIs/extraEnvVariablesAPI` in Playwright files — that module is preload-only and uses IPC).

3. **`faFrontendRenderTimer`** — JSDoc explaining render buffer; usually `FA_FRONTEND_RENDER_TIMER` for components; e2e files may use a **numeric literal** (e.g. `0` or `1000`) when documented in that file.

4. **`selectorList`** — JSDoc `Object of string data selectors` (component) or `...for the e2e` (e2e). Keys are camelCase; values are the exact string stored in **`data-test-locator`** (or another `data-test-*` attribute when the test targets that attribute by name and value), visible labels for `getByText`, or a **full locator string** for rare exceptions (for example `'[role="tooltip"]'` for Quasar portaled tooltips — still centralized in `selectorList`, not hard-coded in the test body; see [DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts](src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/_tests/DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts) `selectorList.quasarTooltip`). When a component uses several `data-test-locator` values that include dynamic suffixes (category keys, ids), keep stable entries in `selectorList` and add a small helper object or functions beside it (see the same file’s `programSettingsSelector`).

5. **Extra timers** — Only when needed (e.g. [checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts) `menuAnimationTimer = 600`; splash screen timeout local `testSplashscreenTimeout` in test).

6. **Inline fixture objects** (when needed) — typed `const` payloads (menus, props, key lists) used in assertions and in `JSON.stringify` for `COMPONENT_PROPS`, declared **in the same Playwright file** before `extraEnvSettings` or beside the test that mutates props.

## Serial suites (`test.describe.serial`) and each `test(...)`

- Group related cases under **`test.describe.serial(...)`** so **one** **`electron.launch`** per group runs in **`test.beforeAll`**, **`firstWindow`**, **`installFaPlaywrightCursorMarkerIfVideoEnabled`**, and **`waitForTimeout(faFrontendRenderTimer)`** once. Store **`let electronApp: ElectronApplication`**, **`let appWindow: Page`**, **`let suiteTestInfo: TestInfo`**; in **`beforeAll`**, assign **`suiteTestInfo = testInfo`**, call **`resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData()`**, then launch with **`...getFaPlaywrightElectronRecordVideoPartial(testInfo)`**. In **`afterAll`**, use **`test.afterAll(async ({}, afterAllTestInfo) => { await closeFaElectronAppWithRecordedVideoAttachments(electronApp, suiteTestInfo, afterAllTestInfo) })`** so WebM attachments show under the suite’s **last** test in the HTML report when the group has **more than one** test. Individual tests use **`async () => { ... }`** and the shared **`appWindow`** (no per-test **`testInfo`** unless you attach something test-scoped).
- **Video**: Pass **`suiteTestInfo`** ( **`beforeAll`** ) as the queue key and **`afterAll`’s** **`TestInfo`** as the third argument so **`recordVideo`** temp dirs dequeue correctly and **`testInfo.attach`** targets a reporter-visible scope (see [playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts](helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts)).
- **Do not** use **`test.describe.parallel`** for root **`playwright.config.ts`** Electron specs unless the user explicitly requests it. Config already sets **`workers: 1`** and **`fullyParallel: false`**.
- **`test.describe.serial.only`** is for **temporary local focus** only; **do not commit** **`.only`** to the default branch.
- **Multiple env snapshots** (e.g. different **`COMPONENT_PROPS`** per [FantasiaMascotImage.playwright.test.ts](src/components/elements/FantasiaMascotImage/_tests/FantasiaMascotImage.playwright.test.ts)): use **separate** top-level **`test.describe.serial`** blocks, each with its own **`beforeAll` / `afterAll`**.
- **UI state between tests**: Order tests so later steps match app state (e.g. dialog **close** last if later tests need an **open** dialog). For Quasar menus that toggle on repeated wrapper clicks, dismiss open panels between tests if needed (see **`dismissOpenMenus`** in [AppControlSingleMenu.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/AppControlSingleMenu/_tests/AppControlSingleMenu.playwright.test.ts)).

Each **`test(...)`** inside a serial suite:

- Precede with a **JSDoc block** describing behavior: a short baseline line (full sentence), then optional ` * - ` detail bullets. Do not wrap one long paragraph across lines mid-sentence; there is no comment line-length limit (see [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) code comments).
- **Title**: readable sentence (often starts with `Check if ...`, `Test if ...`, `Click ...`, `Open ...`).
- **Body pattern** (inside the suite, using shared **`appWindow`**):
  1. `// Prepare the ... locator` — use `appWindow.locator` with a template string and `selectorList` values (same pattern as [GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/GlobalWindowButtons/_tests/GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts)), or `getByText` with `selectorList` entries ([checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts))
  2. `// Check if ...` — `await expect(...).toHaveCount(1)` or equivalent
  3. Interactions, `waitForTimeout` for animations (often `600` ms for menus), `appWindow.evaluate` for `window.faContentBridgeAPIs...` when needed
- Nested callbacks (e.g. `expect.poll`) keep `async () => { ... }` — do not add `testInfo` there unless the callback is a Playwright hook that receives it.
- **1920×1080** (`recordVideo.size`) unless `FA_PLAYWRIGHT_NO_VIDEO` is `'1'` or `'true'`. One **`getFaPlaywrightElectronRecordVideoPartial`** call per **`electron.launch`** (each serial group’s **`beforeAll`**).

## Locators

- **Default**: Prefer **`data-test-locator`** and other `data-test-*` hooks from `.vue` templates for every locator: `appWindow.locator(\`[data-test-locator="${selectorList.someKey}"]\`)` or `appWindow.locator(\`[${selectorList.someDataTestAttributeName}]\`)` when the entry is the full attribute name (for example `data-test-tooltip-text`). Scope under a parent `[data-test-locator="..."]` when the same static child hook appears in multiple rows (category title, setting label, etc.). Do **not** rely on BEM class names or generic Quasar classes unless there is no practical hook.
- **Exceptions** (when `data-test-locator` is impractical): stable **`id`** hooks reserved for accessibility may stay as `#...` only if the component does not mirror them with `data-test-locator` (prefer adding `data-test-locator` on the same node). **`role="*"`** and similar ARIA-driven targets are allowed when asserting portal content (for example Quasar `q-tooltip`); store the **entire** selector string in `selectorList` (for example `quasarTooltip: '[role="tooltip"]'`) and use `appWindow.locator(selectorList.quasarTooltip)` — do **not** scatter raw `[role="tooltip"]` literals in the spec. When **`locator.hover()`** does not wake a small trigger (some Quasar icons under Electron), **`page.mouse.move`** to the element’s **bounding box center** after `scrollIntoViewIfNeeded` is an allowed follow-up for that interaction only ([DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts](src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/_tests/DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts)). **E2E** tests may use **`getByText`** with strings from `selectorList` when exercising real menu or button copy ([checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkDevToolsFunctionality.playwright.spec.ts)).
- **Special menu attributes**: use exactly what the component sets, e.g. `[data-test-menu-test="..."]` and `[data-test-menu-any="..."]` ([AppControlMenus.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/AppControlMenus/_tests/AppControlMenus.playwright.test.ts)).
- **Heavy tooltip suites**: duplicate tooltip body text on the trigger (for example `data-test-tooltip-text` on the help icon) so specs can assert copy without hovering every row; keep **at least one** hover + `selectorList.quasarTooltip` (or your spec’s named entry for the same full string) assertion per suite so real tooltip display stays covered ([DialogProgramSettings.vue](src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/DialogProgramSettings.vue), [DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts](src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/_tests/DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts)). Quasar **`q-tooltip`** content is portaled and delay-based under Electron: prefer **`locator.hover({ force: true })`** over raw **`page.mouse.move`**, give the configured delay plus slack, target the **last** matching **`[role="tooltip"]`** when stale nodes may linger, and wrap the hover + visibility assert in **`expect(async () => { ... }).toPass({ timeout: ... })`** to retry after moving the pointer away to dismiss.
- **WebM cursor visibility**: window capture often omits the OS pointer. After **`firstWindow()`**, call **`installFaPlaywrightCursorMarkerIfVideoEnabled(appWindow)`** from [helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts](helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightElectronRecordVideo.ts) (already wired in existing Electron specs) so recordings show a red dot following synthetic **`mousemove`** positions. Set **`FA_PLAYWRIGHT_CURSOR_MARKER`** to **`0`** or **`false`** to disable; **`FA_PLAYWRIGHT_NO_VIDEO`** skips both video and the marker.

## Shared test data

- **Do not** add a `_tests/_data/` folder. **Production** structured feeds stay under the component’s **`_data/`** (e.g. menu sections, `buttonList`).
- **Playwright fixtures** (props payloads, expected key lists, golden strings) belong **inside** the same `*.playwright.test.ts` as typed **`const`** values — not in a separate **`_tests/<name>.ts`** module whose only job is holding that data. Pass mount data through `COMPONENT_PROPS` / per-test `JSON.stringify` updates (see [AppControlSingleMenu.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/AppControlSingleMenu/_tests/AppControlSingleMenu.playwright.test.ts)).
- Avoid importing `_data` modules that pull Vite-only or heavy i18n graphs into Playwright’s Node loader when a small parallel constant list is enough (e.g. duplicate the key list next to [SocialContactButtons/_data/buttons.ts](src/components/other/SocialContactButtons/_data/buttons.ts) inside the spec with a sync comment).

## Assertions

- Prefer `await expect(locator).toHaveCount(1)` before clicks.
- Use `expect` (non-async) for plain values from `evaluate` when the codebase does ([GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/GlobalWindowButtons/_tests/GlobalWindowButtons.playwright.test.ts) — note existing mix of `await expect` vs `expect` on locators; **follow the immediate surrounding file** for new tests in that folder).
- Avoid `any` in selector maps, test fixtures, and helper signatures; prefer explicit interfaces/types and `unknown` plus narrowing for untyped Playwright values.

## Layout size (width and height)

- **Declared size and caps (default for components)**: When a spec checks **intended** width/height from props or static markup (what the template wired, not necessarily the final laid-out box), assert **`data-test-layout-width`** and **`data-test-layout-height`** on the same node as other `data-test-*` hooks (or domain-specific mirrors such as **`data-test-error-card-width`** on **ErrorCard** for the numeric max-width cap in CSS pixels). Vue should bind these from the same source as the visible sizing props or attributes so the test tracks product intent. This stays stable when the Electron window or parent is narrow and **`max-width: min(100%, …)`** shrinks the rendered box.
- **`boundingBox()` (optional)**: Use **`await locator.boundingBox()`** with rounded comparisons only when you explicitly need **rendered** CSS pixels and the harness guarantees enough viewport/parent space, or when you assert an **inequality** that matches the real CSS contract (for example laid-out width at most the cap).
- **Reference specs**: [FantasiaMascotImage.playwright.test.ts](src/components/elements/FantasiaMascotImage/_tests/FantasiaMascotImage.playwright.test.ts) (**explicit dimensions** group uses **`data-test-layout-*`**), [SocialContactSingleButton.playwright.test.ts](src/components/elements/SocialContactSingleButton/_tests/SocialContactSingleButton.playwright.test.ts) (icon **`data-test-layout-*`** plus **q-img** src), [ErrorCard.playwright.test.ts](src/components/elements/ErrorCard/_tests/ErrorCard.playwright.test.ts) (**`data-test-error-card-width`**), [DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts](src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/_tests/DialogProgramSettings.playwright.test.ts) (no-results **ErrorCard** width cap via the same attribute), [checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts](e2e-tests/checkAppSplashScreen.playwright.spec.ts) (splash **SVG** **`data-test-layout-*`** on **`index.html`**).
- **Native img**: Put **`data-test-locator="fantasiaMascotImage-image"`** on the **`<img>`** itself. Do not chain **`.locator('img')`** under that locator (no nested **`<img>`**); assert **tagName**, **src**, and dimensions on the located node.

## Do not

- Do not use **`test.describe.parallel`** for **`src/components/**`** or **`e2e-tests/**`** Electron Playwright specs unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Do not commit **`test.describe.serial.only`** or other **`.only`** hooks except for short-lived local debugging.
- Do not change `COMPONENT_NAME` / env contract without updating the component testing harness and docs.
- Do not add Playwright (or other) tests whose **system under test** is a file under any **`_data/`** folder; assert behavior through `.vue` or other non-surface that uses that data.
- For Storybook visual snapshot runs (`.storybook-workspace/visual-tests/storybook.visual.playwright.test.ts`), keep these utility Playwright-harness stories excluded because they are not meaningful visual-regression targets: `layouts-componenttestinglayout--with-social-contact-single-button`, `pages-componenttesting--social-contact-single-button`. Component story **`id`** values in **`index.json`** follow **`components-<bucket>-<componentfolder>-<story>`** (for example **`components-elements-fantasiamascotimage--reading`**) when **`meta.title`** is **`Components/<bucket>/<ComponentName>`** — match that shape in **`EXCLUDED_STORY_IDS`** when excluding harness-only component previews.

## TypeScript interfaces and types (`types/`)

- Put shared `interface` / `type` declarations in repository-root `types/` (import with `app/types/...`). Prefer one domain-oriented module per feature area with brief JSDoc on exports (see `types/I_appMenusDataList.ts`). Do not add colocated `<filename>.types.ts` under `src/`, `src-electron/`, or `.storybook-workspace/`. Ambient augmentations for third-party modules also live under `types/` and are loaded with a side-effect import from the owning boot file or `src/stores/index.ts` (see `types/piniaModuleAugmentation.ts`).
- For JavaScript (`.js`), TypeScript (`.ts`), Vue (`.vue`), and JSON (`.json`, `.jsonc`, `.json5`) files, enforce expanded multi-line object literals via ESLint (`object-curly-newline` + `object-property-newline`) and keep files auto-fixable with `eslint --fix`.
